column10:
One of the expected games of this year. I didn’t regret playing Like A Dragon The Man Who Erased His Name. Despite the game only has 5 chapters, Joryu's story has become quite interesting.

Pro"s: 
+ Interesting storyline;
+ Great Characters;
+ Banger soundtracks;
+ Great side quest

Con's
- Higashi's moveset on Coliseum;
- No NG+.

Glad to see Majima, Saejima, Daigo on the game. After spending 26 hours of game I can finally wait for Infinite Wealth. Thank you RGG and Sega for making beautiful game. Hope to see Fist Of The North Star: Lost Paradise on Steam either.
